'''Senne Lammens''' ({{IPA|nl|'sɛnə 'lɑməns|lang}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 February 2025 |title=A Day In The Life {{!}} Goalkeeper Senne Lammens 🧤🎬 #RAFC |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aVkijtmUmZk |access-date=28 February 2026 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Royal Antwerp F.C.]] |language=nl}}</ref> born 7 July 2002) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

Lammens commenced his senior football career at [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]]. At the age of 20, he moved to [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] on a four-year deal. In September 2025, he moved to Manchester United on a deadline day transfer.

Lammens played 28 times for Belgium at youth international level. He made his senior international debut in November 2025.

==Early life==
Senne Lammens<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4407896/202526-premier-league-squad-lists |title=2025/26 Premier League squad lists |publisher=Premier League |date=12 September 2025 |access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref> was born on 7 July 2002 in [[Zottegem]], East Flanders.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe516008/senne-lammens/ |title=Senne Lammens: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |date=<!-- citation bot adds wrong date --> |access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Club Brugge===
Lammens came through the youth systems of [[KRC Bambrugge]], [[F.C.V. Dender E.H.|Dender]] and [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].<ref>{{cite news |title=16-jarige Senne Lammens maakt droom waar: met Club Brugge mee naar Champions League |trans-title=16-year-old Senne Lammens sees dream come true: travelling with Club Brugge to the Champions League |url=https://www.hln.be/in-de-buurt/erpe-mere/16-jarige-senne-lammens-maakt-droom-waar-met-club-brugge-mee-naar-champions-league~a3234bdf/ |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |language=nl |date=2 October 2018 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> On 3 October 2018 he was included in the first-team matchday squad for the [[UEFA Champions League]] group match away to [[Atlético Madrid]], aged 16.<ref>{{cite news |title=Club Brugge vertrokken naar Madrid: Leko laat twee spelers thuis, maar neemt 16-jarige doelman mee |trans-title=Club Brugge depart for Madrid: Leko leaves two players at home, but takes 16-year-old goalkeeper |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20181002_03801640 |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=2 October 2018 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

On 11 December 2019, then 17-year-old Lammens scored a stoppage-time headed equaliser to make it 2–2 for Club Brugge's under-19s against [[Real Madrid CF (youth)|Real Madrid's under-19s]] in the [[UEFA Youth League]] group stage; the result secured Brugge's progress to the knockout phase.<ref>{{cite news |title=U19 Club Brugge spelen gelijk tegen Real Madrid in Youth League na kopbalgoal van doelman in slotseconden |trans-title=Club Brugge U19 draw with Real Madrid in Youth League after goalkeeper's headed goal in the final seconds |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20191211_04761885 |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=11 December 2019 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

He featured for [[Club NXT]]—Club Brugge's U23 side—in the [[Belgian First Division B|First Division B]] during the 2020–21 season, the team's debut campaign at that level.<ref name="auto">{{cite news |title=Hallucinante ontknoping op Jan Breydel: De Ketelaere voorkomt in minuut 103 (!) nederlaag van Club tegen Eupen |trans-title=Hallucinatory finale at Jan Breydel: De Ketelaere prevents defeat for Club against Eupen in the 103rd minute |url=https://www.hln.be/jupiler-pro-league/hallucinante-ontknoping-op-jan-breydel-de-ketelaere-voorkomt-in-minuut-103-nederlaag-van-club-tegen-eupen~aa07dd2e4/ |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |language=nl |date=25 July 2021 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

With first-choice goalkeeper [[Simon Mignolet]] injured, Lammens started for the senior side in the [[2021 Belgian Super Cup|Belgian Super Cup]] on 17 July 2021, a 3–2 win over [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Club Brugge klopt Racing Genk en steekt Supercup op zak na spectaculaire minuten net voor en net na rust |trans-title=Club Brugge beat Racing Genk and pocket the Super Cup after spectacular minutes before and after half-time |url=https://www.hln.be/dossier-club-brugge-opent-nieuwe-seizoen-met-winst-in-super-cup/live-supercup-brugse-goalie-lammens-toont-zich-met-enkele-prima-reddingen-club-op-weg-naar-zestiende-supercup~a7db21e9/ |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |language=nl |date=17 July 2021 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=19-jarige doelman Senne Lammens zet ondanks foutje ijzersterke prestatie neer in vuurdoop: "Koele kikker, die weet wat hij wil" |trans-title=19-year-old goalkeeper Senne Lammens delivers a strong debut despite a mistake: "Cool customer who knows what he wants" |url=https://www.hln.be/club-brugge/br-br-19-jarige-doelman-senne-lammens-zet-ondanks-foutje-ijzersterke-prestatie-neer-in-vuurdoop-koele-kikker-die-weet-wat-hij-wil~aeae805e/ |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |language=nl |date=17 July 2021 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> He started again on the opening matchday of the [[Belgian Pro League|Pro League]] season on 25 July 2021 against [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]], and later appeared in a 3–0 [[Belgian Cup|Croky Cup]] win over [[K.M.S.K. Deinze|Deinze]] on 27 October 2021.<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Verloren zonen Izquierdo en Dost schieten Club Brugge in Croky Cup voorbij tienkoppig Deinze |trans-title=Prodigal sons Izquierdo and Dost fire Club Brugge past ten-man Deinze in the Croky Cup |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/330129 |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=27 October 2021 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> On 22 May 2022 he came on as a second-half substitute for Mignolet in the final match of the champions' play-offs against [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Geen perfect afscheid voor Alfred Schreuder: Club Brugge slikt in het slot knullige gelijkmaker tegen Anderlecht |trans-title=No perfect farewell for Alfred Schreuder: Club Brugge concede a clumsy late equaliser against Anderlecht |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/342874 |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=22 May 2022 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

===Antwerp===
On 8 June 2023, Lammens left Club Brugge at the end of his contract and signed a four-year deal with [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Antwerp]], then the reigning Belgian champions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Doelman Senne Lammens tekent contract bij RAFC |trans-title=Goalkeeper Senne Lammens signs contract with RAFC |url=https://royalantwerpfc.be/nieuws/doelman-senne-lammens-tekent-contract-bij-rafc |website=Royal Antwerp FC |language=nl |date=8 June 2023 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> He made his senior Antwerp debut on 1 November 2023, starting a 4–1 [[Belgian Cup]] win away to [[Lierse S.K. (2018)|Lierse]]; coach [[Mark van Bommel]] had indicated beforehand that Lammens would be considered for the tie.<ref>{{cite news |title=Antwerp is maatje te groot voor Lierse en bekert verder na aangenaam duel met 5 goals |url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2023-2024/1-16-finale/01/lierse-k-antwerp-antwerp-is-maatje-te-groot-voor-lierse-en-bekert-verder-na-aangenaam-duel-met-5-goals~1694507477492/ |website=Sporza |language=nl |date=1 November 2023 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Antwerp haalt uit tegen moedig Lierse en tankt vertrouwen |url=https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20231101_93562062 |work=Gazet van Antwerpen |language=nl |date=1 November 2023 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Van Bommel laat in kaarten kijken: drie debutanten bij Antwerp? |url=https://www.voetbalnieuws.be/news/740717/van-bommel-laat-in-kaarten-kijken-3-debutanten-bij-antwerp |work=VoetbalNieuws |language=nl |date=31 October 2023 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

During the [[2023–24 Royal Antwerp F.C. season|2023–24 season]] he served primarily as understudy to [[Jean Butez]], featuring again in the domestic cup, including a December tie against [[Lierse S.K. (2018)|Lierse]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Antwerp-doelman Senne Lammens krijgt nieuwe kans in bekerduel tegen Lierse |url=https://app.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20231205_95066666 |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=5 December 2023 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> By the start of the [[2024–25 Royal Antwerp F.C. season|2024–25 season]] he had established himself as Antwerp's first-choice goalkeeper ahead of Butez, a change noted widely in Belgian coverage.<ref>{{cite news |title=Geen transfer en in de schaduw van nieuwe nummer één: hoe is het nog met Jean Butez? |url=https://www.hln.be/antwerp/geen-transfer-en-in-de-schaduw-van-nieuwe-nummer-een-senne-lammens-hoe-zou-het-nog-zijn-met-antwerp-doelman-jean-butez~a889c38b/ |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |language=nl |date=14 September 2024 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Veel geduld getoond, nu van goudwaarde: Senne Lammens overschouwt zijn doorbraak |url=https://sporza.be/nl/2024/11/13/veel-geduld-getoond-nu-van-goudwaarde-voor-jonge-duivels-en-antwerp-senne-lammens-overschouwt-zijn-definitieve-doorbraak~1731511505365/ |work=Sporza |language=nl |date=14 November 2024 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Como en Antwerp onderhandelen over Jean Butez |url=https://www.gva.be/sport/voetbal/como-en-antwerp-onderhandelen-over-jean-butez/37660694.html |work=Gazet van Antwerpen |language=nl |date=19 December 2024 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

Lammens' performances in 2024–25 drew particular notice for shot-stopping and penalty saves; by mid-February he had saved four penalties in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |title=Interview. "De eerste keer dat ik het hoorde, dacht ik: amai...": Senne Lammens over geruchten rond Man United, zijn penaltygeheim en toekomst bij Antwerp |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sport/voetbal/interview.-de-eerste-keer-dat-ik-het-hoorde-dacht-ik-amai...-senne-lammens-over-geruchten-rond-man-united-zijn-penaltygeheim-en-toekomst-bij-antwerp/41011709.html |work=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |date=15 February 2025 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> He was also a regular winner of Antwerp's fan-voted Player of the Month award during the season, including November 2024 and March 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jullie Player of the Month november... Senne Lammens! |url=https://www.facebook.com/RoyalAntwerpFC/posts/jullie-player-of-the-month-november-senne-lammens-rafc-antwerpfirst/1007557368069526/ |website=Royal Antwerp FC (Facebook) |language=nl |date=30 November 2024 |access-date=17 August 2025 |quote=Jullie Player of the Month november... Senne Lammens!}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bezoekje aan Bosuil blijft bondscoach Rudi Garcia bij: drie Antwerp-spelers in voorselectie Rode Duivels |url=https://www.gva.be/sport/voetbal/bezoekje-aan-bosuil-is-bondscoach-rudi-garcia-bijgebleven-drie-antwerp-spelers-in-voorselectie-rode-duivels/47400266.html |work=Gazet van Antwerpen |language=nl |date=6 March 2025 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Oud-doelman Frank Boeckx: "Over enkele jaren kan hij de fakkel overnemen van Courtois" |url=https://www.gva.be/incoming/over-enkele-jaren-kan-hij-de-fakkel-overnemen-van-courtois-oud-doelman-en-analist-frank-boeckx-vindt-senne-lammens-antwerp-een-logische-rode-duivel/49207814.html |work=Gazet van Antwerpen |language=nl |date=14 March 2025 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

===Manchester United===
On 1 September 2025, [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] signed Lammens in a deadline day move from [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] for a reported transfer fee of £18.1m.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 September 2025 |title=Transfer news: United sign Senne Lammens |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/transfer-news-man-utd-sign-senne-lammens-from-royal-antwerp|access-date=1 September 2025 |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Lammens joins Man Utd from Royal Antwerp |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cr5r5m9p99mo |date=1 September 2025 |access-date=2 September 2025 |work=BBC Sport|first=Steve|last=Sutcliffe}}</ref>

Lammens made his debut on 4 October 2025 and kept the first clean sheet of the season for Manchester United against newly promoted [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] in a 2–0 home victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cgj1e8w82l5o|title=Senne Lammens: Man Utd goalkeeper serenaded on debut|first=Simon|last=Stone|date=4 October 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

In his debut season at Manchester United, Lammens was named the [[2025–26 Premier League#Annual awards|2025–26 Premier League Transfer of the Season]], an award recognising the player judged to have made the biggest impact for his new club in the season.<ref name="tots">{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4672279/lammens-named-barclays-transfer-of-the-season |title=Lammens named Barclays Transfer of the Season |website=Premier League |date=1 June 2026 |access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2025, Lammens was named in the senior [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] squad for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League]] [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League promotion/relegation play-offs|play-off]] matches against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] on 20 and 23 March 2025, respectively.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://sporza.be/nl/2025/03/13/rudi-garcia-slaat-nieuwe-weg-in-met-4-debutanten-in-eerste-selectie-ook-courtois-keert-officieel-terug~1741863334162/| title=Rudi Garcia slaat nieuwe weg in met 4 debutanten in eerste selectie, ook Courtois keert officieel terug | trans-title=Rudi Garcia takes new path with 4 debutants in first selection, Courtois also officially returns | publisher=sporza | access-date=26 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=De eerste selectie van bondscoach Rudi Garcia |url=https://www.rbfa.be/nl/nieuws/de-eerste-selectie-van-bondscoach-rudi-garcia |website=Royal Belgian FA |language=nl |date=14 March 2025 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Courtois return to Belgium squad after lengthy absence |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/courtois-return-belgium-squad-after-lengthy-absence-2025-03-14/ |work=Reuters |date=14 March 2025 |access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

On 18 November 2025, Lammens made his senior debut for Belgium, keeping a clean sheet in a 7–0 [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifying]] win against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Dorgu denied at the death as Lammens makes international bow |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/internationals-round-up-lammens-debut-and-dorgu-denied |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=19 November 2025 |access-date=19 November 2025}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, he was named in Belgium's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/belgium-squad-garcia-lukaku-named |title=Belgium squad named for FIFA World Cup 2026 |website=FIFA |date=15 May 2026 |access-date=3 June 2026}}</ref>

